    "System.Description": "<div>Business case:&nbsp;<br> </div><div>We want to test the new Enhanced PDP on Forbes traffic&nbsp; </div><div><br> </div><div>Ask:<br>Dupe&nbsp;<a href=\"https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/testosterone-1\">https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/testosterone-1</a>&nbsp;<br>to create&nbsp;<a href=\"https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/forbes/testosterone\">https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/forbes/testosterone</a>&nbsp; </div><div><br> </div><div>On the new page - add the Forbes banner seen on&nbsp;<a target=_blank href=\"https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/forbes\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color:#1264a3;\">https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/forbes</a>&nbsp; </div><div><br> </div><div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Copy update:&nbsp;</span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Needle-free testosterone options available with the At-Home Testosterone Testing Kit<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">-&gt;&nbsp;</span></span> </div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">Needle-free testosterone options available with the Testosterone Test</span></span> </div><br> </div><div><br> </div>",
    "Microsoft.VSTS.Common.AcceptanceCriteria": "<div>New page is live with additional banner&nbsp; </div>",
    "Custom.TechnicalPlan": "## Requirements Readiness\n\n**Overall:** Sufficient\n\n**Sources reviewed:**\n- Spec doc (wiki): Not available — not required for this scope\n- Design (Figma): Not available — not required, changes are mechanical\n- Work item description: Clear and complete — specifies source URL, target URL, Forbes banner source, and exact copy change\n- Parent/child work items: None linked\n- Prior art: `page-mens-opt-comparison-forbes.php` demonstrates the exact pattern for adding a Forbes linkbar to a page variant\n\n**Gaps and clarifications needed:**\n- None — all information needed to implement is present\n\n**Plan confidence:** High — straightforward LP dupe with two well-defined additions\n\n## Context and Goal\n\nDuplicate the Enhanced PDP (`mens-opt/testosterone-1`) to a new Forbes-targeted variant at `mens-opt/forbes/testosterone`. Add the Forbes linkbar banner and update one line of copy. Intended for A/B testing Forbes ad traffic against the Enhanced PDP.\n\n## Design\n\n**New slug:** `mens-opt-forbes-testosterone`\n\nAll four naming artifacts must match exactly per convention.\n\n**Files to create:**\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `src/page-mens-opt-forbes-testosterone.php` | Copy of `page-mens-opt-enhanced-pdp.php` with 3 targeted changes |\n| `src/static/scss/pages/mens-opt-forbes-testosterone.scss` | Copy of `mens-opt-enhanced-pdp.scss` with root selector renamed + linkbar color |\n| `src/static/js/pages/mens-opt-forbes-testosterone.bundle.js` | Copy of `mens-opt-enhanced-pdp.bundle.js` — identical logic, no changes needed |\n\n**File to modify:**\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/functions.php` | Add `'mens-opt-forbes-testosterone'` to `HONE_PAGE_TEMPLATES` array |\n\n**PHP template changes (vs source `page-mens-opt-enhanced-pdp.php`):**\n\n1. Template header — change template name and slug:\n   - `// Template Name: Mens OPT Forbes Testosterone`\n   - `$template_name = 'mens-opt-forbes-testosterone';`\n\n2. Add Forbes linkbar — add `$linkbar_vars` to global declaration, set value, and include template part after `get_header()`:\n   - `$linkbar_vars = ['linkbar_content' =&gt; 'Seen in Forbes Health Best TRT Clinic of 2025'];`\n   - `require_once get_template_directory() . '/template-parts/linkbar.php';`\n\n3. Copy update in the `.alternatives` section:\n   - From: &quot;Needle-free testosterone options available with the At-Home Testosterone Testing Kit&quot;\n   - To: &quot;Needle-free testosterone options available with the Testosterone Test&quot;\n\n**SCSS changes:** Replace root selector `.mens-opt-enhanced-pdp` → `.mens-opt-forbes-testosterone` throughout, and add linkbar text color:\n```\n.linkbar a {\n    color: #0e0b20;\n}\n```\n\n**WordPress admin (manual step):** Create a new page in WP admin with:\n- Slug: `testosterone`\n- Parent page: `mens-opt/forbes`\n- Page template: &quot;Mens OPT Forbes Testosterone&quot;\n\nThis produces the URL: `https://buy.honehealth.com/mens-opt/forbes/testosterone`\n\n## Testing\n\n- Build: run `yarn build` from theme directory, verify no compile errors\n- Spot check on staging:\n  - Forbes linkbar appears at top with correct text\n  - Updated copy reads &quot;Testosterone Test&quot; in the alternatives section\n  - All carousels, videos, FAQs, and CTAs function identically to the source page\n- Verify `mens-opt/testosterone-1` is unaffected\n\n## Architecture Review\n\nNot needed. Content/template duplication with no new systems, no schema changes, no data model changes, no core service changes, and no impact on shared infrastructure or user journeys beyond adding a new URL.\n\n## Agent Executability Assessment\n\n**Overall:** Fully executable\n\n**Executable by agent:**\n- PHP template file creation: mechanical copy + 3 targeted changes, all well-defined\n- SCSS file creation: copy + single root class rename + one style addition\n- JS bundle file creation: identical copy, no changes\n- `functions.php` update: add one string to an array — well-defined pattern\n\n**Requires human:**\n- WordPress admin page creation: must be done manually in WP admin to set parent page, slug, and template assignment\n- Post-deploy verification: spot check on staging/prod\n\n**Prerequisites for agent execution:**\n- None — no dependent PRs, no data fixes, no blocked work\n\n## Agent Confidence Assessment\n\n**Task type:** New feature\n**Estimated complexity:** Low\n**Agentibility:** Agent-ready\n**Rationale:** Mechanical LP duplication with well-defined file patterns, clear source files to copy, and two targeted content changes. All changes follow established patterns in the codebase.\n**Suggested next step:** Assign to agent for code implementation; human handles WP admin page creation and post-deploy spot check.\n",
